commit.message:
grate: support fragment uniforms

Fragment shader uniforms, defined in the assembly, are exposed to the shader user.

Example:

.uniforms
	[1]   = "uniform_1_fp20";
	[2].l = "uniform_2_fx10_low";
	[2].h = "uniform_2_fx10_high";

The BLOB's symbol location encoding is reused, so grate_3d_ctx_set_fragment_uniform()
also works for the cgc-generated shaders.

